HEADWORD: Flipe
<hw>Flipe</hw> <pr>(fl⟦imac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To turn
inside out, or with the leg part back over the foot, as a stocking in
pulling off or for putting on.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

